The King Sabata Dalindyebo municipal council has mandated its Municipal Public Accounts Committee (MPAC) to investigate R5.2-million fruitless and wasteful expenditure incurred by the municipality in the 2015-16 financial year. The decision was taken at a recent council meeting in which KSD mayor Dumani Zozo presented a report on the expenditure asking council to write off the debt.The Dispatch is in possession of the mayor s report on the shock spend, attributed to interest charged by service providers.Read more in the Dispatch today.